Quote:  BULLEY (TOITOI) <i>Gobiomorphus gobioides</i> (Cuv. and Val.) The bulley is one of the most abundant of our native freshwater fish. It is often referred to as a close relative of the

Kokopu (<i>Galaxias fasciatus</i>) ... This is not correct ... The Bulley, or Bullhead as it is known in some parts, forms an important food for the introduced Trout throughout New Zealand.
